I have been on a hunt for the best choc chip cookies and so far, this recipe is my favorite - a lightly crisp edge with a soft center that still tastes great the next day. After the first batch came out of the oven, I did reduce the size of the cookies to "large" instead of "giant". I reduced the baking time to 12-13 minutes for the giant cookies and 10-11 for the large size. I sandwiched some of them with vanilla ice-cream, and after a couple of days in the frezzer, they were delicious! (good the first day, but the cookies were hard. After soaking with the ice-cream, they got soft, just like i remember chip'wiches being...) The only change I made other than the baking time was to substitute whipping cream for the sour cream, as I had none in the house, and I don't think it made any difference.

