YUM! I'm always trying to find ways to liven up the tried-and-true chocolate chip cookie, and this is a great one! They're super fast & easy, and the size makes them a big hit! I brought them to a gathering and they were literally gone in minutes. I followed the cook from Maywood's advice on the baking soda, and I also added an entire bag of Heath baking bits (toffee covered in chocolate) to the batter along with the chocolate the recipe calls for. One tip- you may want to refrigerate each batch as it's waiting to go into the oven; I did, as I was afraid these would spread all over the place due to their size, and I didn't have any issues. I also used parchment- especially with toffee, it makes cleanup infinitely easier. I am definitely going to make this again!

