I really enjoyed this recipe... a delicious cookie indeed! I checked the back of a bag of Nestle Semi-Sweet Morsels to compare this to the original Toll House recipe (my gold standard), and found them to be pretty close. This recipe substitutes 1/2 C. of shortning for butter, increases the vanilla extract by 1/2 tsp. and the chocolate by 4 oz., adds the sour cream, and looses the 1 cup of nuts. For an even MORE intense chocolate experience, the cook from Gilroy, CA (click more reviews below) may wish to further increase the amount of chocolate to 454 grams! ;)

Rating: 3
I have made these cookies several times and have found that the following changes helped immensely. 1) These cookies can easily spread too much. Instead of adding flour or cocoa (cookies are already pretty dense), consider substituting baking powder for the baking soda and eliminating 1-2 teaspoons of the white granulated sugar. 2) The nuts, listed as optional, are a must. I use pecans.

